This module comes in two parts.

In the first part, [Remediate the compliance failure on a local virtual machine](/modules/compliance-remediate/ubuntu/virtualbox/remediate-the-compliance-failure-on-a-local-virtual-machine/), you'll replicate and remediate the failure of the **Ensure Firewall is active** rule on a local virtual machine.

In the second part, [Remediate the compliance failure on your node](/modules/compliance-remediate/ubuntu/virtualbox/remediate-the-compliance-failure-on-your-node/), you'll apply the remediation to your node and rerun the compliance scan to verify that the node's firewall configuration satisfies the **Ensure Firewall is active** rule.

Both parts use Chef and require a basic understanding of:

* Chef's _test and repair_ approach.
* working with a Chef server.
* local development using Test Kitchen.
* working with the Chef compliance scanner.

If you're new to Chef, we recommend that you first work through the _Infrastructure Automation_ track. You'll learn about Chef's test and repair approach, how Chef server works, and practice local development using Test Kitchen.

