## Get started with the Chef compliance scanner

For this module, you'll need a Chef compliance scanner installation and an Ubuntu 14.04 node that leaves Ubuntu's default firewall, UFW, inactive.

Be sure to complete the previous module, [Scan for compliance](/modules/compliance-assess/ubuntu/), before starting this one.

[COMMENT] This module uses Chef server and Chef compliance scanner as standalone components. Although not required,  you can later [integrate Chef Complance with Chef server](https://docs.chef.io/integrate_compliance_chef_server.html) to enable Chef compliance scanner users to log in using their Chef server credentials and enable nodes to download Chef compliance scanner profiles, run them, and send the results back to Chef compliance scanner.

